Before modifying ranked HMM
TODO: Ranked HMM, map merge

Top k map-matching implemented, nearest neighbour map merge implemented but not tested yet. Map inference not runnable due to a bug in the final step.
TODO: fix the bug in map inference, test map merge and evaluate, add confidence score and influence score, check the code correctness of map-matching

Map inference bug fixed, map inference result visible.

Rewrite the unmatched trajectory selection strategy and the break point logic.
TODO: Refine the top-k matching result generation, test the map merge and evaluation, add confidence score and influence score

A bunch of data analysis is done. Input road ways now are categorized by road level, road type, the unfolding visualization is completely rewritten to support various color based on road visit frequency, trajectory comparison and multiple map layer. A few map-matching bugs fixed.
TODO: add confidence score and influence score, test the map merge and evaluation.

Both confidence score and influence score are added, map merge, co-optimization model and result refinement are implemented. The iteration is runnable now but the map merge need to be improved to enable a reasonable iteration. The visualization is rewritten, now it has a separate entrance for map visualization and the map and trajectory visualization is separated. The map-matching evaluation is changed to evaluate based on length.
TODO: Check the map-matching correctness, especially the top-k version. Redesign the map-merge to provide meaningful output. Change the road removal strategy.

Basic functionality complete, map merge and road removal is improved. Ground-truth map-matching reaches 98% precision and 99% recall. Start to focus on optimization
